A "blood buffer" refers to a chemical system within the blood, that helps maintain a stable pH level by neutralizing added acids or bases, ensuring proper bodily functions can occur;
Plasmais the liquid component of blood, in which the red blood cells, white blood cells, and platelets are suspended.Plasmais the component of blood that acts as the major buffer, maintaining a normal pH level that supports cell function.
